Module HW08
Package provided.discovery.impl.model

Interface IDiscoveryModelToViewAdapter<TRemoteStub>

Type Parameters:
TRemoteStub - The type of stub to which the discovery server's endpoints are referencing
public interface IDiscoveryModelToViewAdapter<TRemoteStub>
Adapter used by some ADiscoveryModel implementations to connect to their "view".
Author:
swong

  • Method Summary

    Modifier and Type Method Description
    void addStub​(TRemoteStub stub)
    Add the given stub to the rest of the world (i.e the "view") Called when a discovery model has retrieved a stub using an endpoint pulled from the discovery server.
    static <T> IDiscoveryModelToViewAdapter<T> makeNullAdapter()
    Factory to create a null adapter.

  • Method Details

    • addStub

      void addStub​(TRemoteStub stub)
      Add the given stub to the rest of the world (i.e the "view") Called when a discovery model has retrieved a stub using an endpoint pulled from the discovery server.
      Parameters:
      stub - The stub to add.

    • makeNullAdapter

      static <T> IDiscoveryModelToViewAdapter<T> makeNullAdapter()
      Factory to create a null adapter. A factory is needed because the adapter requires generic types, which the compiler will deduce from the variable to which the resultant adapter is assigned.
      Type Parameters:
      T - The TRemoteStub generic type of the IDiscoveryModelToViewAdapter variable to which this adapter will be assigned.
      Returns:
      A no-op adapter
